race.comment: BLUE EYED BRIGID (8) will be at her peak fourth-up and can improve sharply over this trip. Struck trouble early and forced to cover ground on the turn when fifth over 1600m at Gosford. In-form jockey goes aboard and can race a little closer from the gate. SILVER TEMPEST (3) was rewarded for his consistency when demolishing a maiden field over 1600m at Gosford. Ready to go on with it now and will have little trouble running the 1800m out. CARAVANSERAI (2) is going nicely through his grades this time in with two wins from his last four starts. Should be able to take control early and give plenty of cheek. STAY TUNED (6) on the quick backup after coming out of a decent contest when fourth over 1600m at Newcastle in BM64 class. Look for him late.
